I still love these photos @erik.melvin took in my old studio, happy new year ya'll. Not sure I want to share too much about my year as I feel like I’m still in a state of flux and working to understand myself better, but I’m very grateful for my family and friends and everyone who has collected my work and supported me and inspired me. I really hope next year I make my dreams come true. Stay safe and take care and I’ll see you soon after I take a break on here.

I’m excited to share my stay with Hotel June West! It was my second time staying here and I loved it even more this time thanks to the impeccable quality of the staff, food, and vacation vibes. Staying in a hotel is still a luxury experience to me and something I cherish especially being so close to the ocean! Highly recommend bookending your summer travels in and out of LAX by staying here. Don’t skip the mezcal flight presented by Jordan who grew my admiration for the art of mezcal even more. Plus the daybed experience during a pool party is all lil me could ever dream of. From now til 7/23 you can book with 15% off using code MARLEIGH15 or my link in bio and use that towards a The Getaway cocktail or happy hour oysters. Dog-friendly, comfy beds, Aesop products… say less. Thank you again @hoteljunewestla and @caravanswimclub, now finding excuses to stay with you again 🫶🏼

ANNOUNCING my gallery debut in Los Angeles at @tappancollective’s gallery 9/28 6–9p🩶 I’ll have a 72”x48” diptych on display inspired by southern California’s landscape. Hoping to see you there!!!! Please RSVP at the link in my bio 🩶

Life is Life-ing Pt. I
1. Summertime in Richmond, VA with the insane cocktails @littlenickelgram.

2. Mommy and Sadie in Indiana visiting my family during a sad time.

3. Nana in her kitchen with Sadie and her fridge pasted with memories, the home phone she always answers.

4. My nana’s bathroom which has changed so much over time. I used to dig through her cabinets when she wasn’t looking and would try on every shade of Clinique lipstick she had.

5. The dining room that hasn’t aged unlike the rest of her house, and I never want it to. We have Christmas supper here every year. As children we were too focused about what was under the tree to finish her delicious and famous cordon-bleu.

6. If you couldn’t tell my nana was Scottish well I think you know now.

7. Mommy and Sadie and some mimosas we made on a visit to Nana’s.

8. Dad and Mom in the house they’ve lived in for 25 years and counting.

9. Dad and Sadie in the garden.

10. Bay-bay in front of our favorite Stellas after a girl date.

Life is Life-ing Pt. II

1. A cool night at the place of Hollywood history, the Future Perfect Goldwyn house, for an Ardray whisky event.

2. Sadie during a road trip up the west coast to Seattle.

3. Nick and Sadie and our favorite royal milk tea from Stereoscope.

4. Nature’s visual aphrodisiac.

5. The coolest Rachel and Sadie at dinner.

6. Dean looking cool as usual.

7. The squid, white bean and arugula salad I dream endlessly about from Edo’s.

8. Melina eating banana pudding on a very hot day.

9. Melon whisky cocktails at the Ardray event.

Life is Life-ing Pt. III

1. Beans, say less.

2. Nick and a surprise friend.

3. Girl things.

4. Corn pasta.

5. Hi.

6. A fav chocolate brand, Compartés. 

7. Nick at his first sold out Cafe Triste pop-up, so proud of you.

8. Nick chopping it up.

9. Nick and I, thanks for letting me be your sous, chef.

10. First time camping with my dream girl dinner.

In her new capsule series, Culver found herself drawn to many of the same colors and gestures as are found in other recent works. There’s both comfort and challenge in repetition, as Culver embraces contrast in herself and in her own work. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“My favorite thing about these works is that they are organic, made without sketches and I use a slapping motion of the brush filled with diluted paint as a tool so I don’t dictate the nature of the paint too much. There’s a surprise element to the process of these paintings that represent subconscious movement and feeling.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

2023 was a strange year, some major highlights and excitement and a lot of sadness and loss. I’m just grateful for my health and lessons and my only focus right now is body health and painting. I’m in an introspective hermit mode right now which is due to a slow and strange work year and hoping in 2024 I’ll be out of my cocoon a bit more. Thank you so much for your kindness, support and love of my work and of me. It’s so important to embrace your community and show those around you love. Thank you to @_stone_thrower_ for these photos!!!

Los Angeles, I’m very excited to announce my first solo show with @keystoneartla on Feb. 3rd. I’ll have paintings on view and am very excited and grateful for this opportunity because having a show in LA has been on my bucket list for 2024. You can sign up for a show invite via email and also a postcard in the mail if you like! Link in bio 🩶 If you can’t make it to LA while the show is up 2/1-2/12, the paintings will be on Tappan in April and you can always email me with questions and requests!
